    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Doton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 5 (Spell Level 3)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 4</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 18 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 6 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 18</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>This technique is the opposite of Chi Katame no Jutsu, and will turn 1 cubic ft of stone to sand each round. You choose precisely what area is softened. If the target area contains rock belonging to a manufactured object or structure, it can make a Fortitude save at a +4 bonus to resist the transformation. Structures so transformed take 1d10 damage per round this technique remains active on its area. You can only have one instance of this technique active at a time (including usage by clones).</p>\n\n\n\n",
